-- Table: acquirer_countries
COMMENT ON TABLE main.acquirer_countries IS 'Mapping of payment acquirers to ISO country codes. Primary key: `row_index`. Links `acquirer` entities to geographic jurisdictions. 8 rows. (8 rows)';

COMMENT ON COLUMN main.acquirer_countries.row_index IS '[identifier] Zero-based sequential position or index of the country record. (BIGINT, 9 distinct, range: 0..7)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.acquirer_countries.acquirer IS '[categorical] Acquiring institution name; categorical identifier for financial entities. (VARCHAR, 9 distinct, range: bank_of_springfield..the_savings_and_loan_bank, avg 15 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.acquirer_countries.country_code IS '[categorical] ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code for the payment acquirer. (VARCHAR, 5 distinct, range: FR..US, avg 2 chars)';

-- View: fee_rules_expanded
COMMENT ON VIEW main.fee_rules_expanded IS 'Granular fee structure mapping for transaction processing. Links `fees_id` to card schemes, account types, and interchange indicators (ACI). Defines cost logic via `fees_fixed_amount` and `fees_rate` based on cross-border status, MCC, capture latency, and merchant performance metrics (volume/fraud). Use for precise transaction cost calculation and margin analysis. (102,932 rows). Fee rules with NULL wildcards pre-expanded for 4 dimensions (account_type, aci, is_credit, intracountry). Use simple WHERE equality on expanded_* columns. 5 other dimensions still need OR IS NULL. For merchant-specific queries use merchant_transaction_fees instead.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fee_rules_expanded.fees_id IS '[identifier] Primary key for fee rule definitions. (BIGINT, 1,232 distinct, range: 1..1000). Fee rule ID. Multiple expanded rows per fees_id — GROUP BY fees_id to deduplicate when averaging.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fee_rules_expanded.fees_card_scheme IS '[categorical] Card network or payment scheme name associated with the fee rule. (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, range: GlobalCard..TransactPlus, avg 10 chars). NOT expanded — use exact match. NULL means matches all schemes.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fee_rules_expanded.expanded_account_type IS '[categorical] Single-character account classification code (R, F, H, S) for fee calculation logic. (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, range: D..S, avg 1 chars). Pre-expanded from NULL wildcard. Use simple WHERE equality.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fee_rules_expanded.expanded_aci IS '[categorical] Single-character fee rule classification code. (VARCHAR, 6 distinct, range: A..F, avg 1 chars). Pre-expanded values A-F only. ACI G is NOT included — use raw fees table for G.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fee_rules_expanded.expanded_is_credit IS '[flag] Indicates if the fee rule represents a credit adjustment rather than a charge. (BOOLEAN, 2 distinct, range: false..true). Pre-expanded: TRUE or FALSE. Use simple WHERE equality.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fee_rules_expanded.expanded_intracountry IS '[flag] Boolean indicator for intra-country fee application logic; 1.0 for active, 0.0 for inactive. (DECIMAL(2,1), 2 distinct, range: 0.0..1.0). Pre-expanded: 1.0=domestic, 0.0=international.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fee_rules_expanded.fees_fixed_amount IS '[measure] Flat monetary surcharge applied per transaction according to fee rules. (DOUBLE, 13 distinct, range: 0.0..0.14). Fixed fee component in euros.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fee_rules_expanded.fees_rate IS '[measure] Fee percentage or basis points applied to transactions; integer values ranging from 10 to 99. (BIGINT, 82 distinct, range: 10..99). Basis points. Fee = fees_fixed_amount + (fees_rate * eur_amount / 10000).';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fee_rules_expanded.fees_mcc IS '[categorical] Merchant Category Code (MCC) associated with fee calculation rules. (BIGINT, 57 distinct, 2% null, range: 3000..9399). NOT expanded — still requires OR IS NULL for wildcard matching.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fee_rules_expanded.fees_capture_delay IS '[categorical] Timeframe or trigger for fee collection. Values: ''manual'', ''immediate'', or numeric ranges (e.g., ''>5'', ''3-5''). (VARCHAR, 5 distinct, 52% null, range: 3-5..manual, avg 4 chars). NOT expanded — still requires OR IS NULL. Values: <3, 3-5, >5, immediate, manual.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fee_rules_expanded.fees_monthly_volume IS '[categorical] Tiered monthly transaction volume brackets for fee calculation rules. (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, 81% null, range: 100k-1m..>5m, avg 5 chars). NOT expanded — still requires OR IS NULL.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fee_rules_expanded.fees_monthly_fraud_level IS '[categorical] Binned monthly fraud percentage ranges used for fee calculation logic. (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, 90% null, range: 7.2%-7.7%..>8.3%, avg 7 chars). NOT expanded — still requires OR IS NULL.';

-- Table: fees
COMMENT ON TABLE main.fees IS 'Fee schedule for payment processing. Links transaction attributes (card_scheme, is_credit, account_type, aci, merchant_category_code) and volume metrics (monthly_volume, monthly_fraud_level) to pricing structures (fixed_amount, rate). Used for calculating interchange and processing costs based on capture_delay and geographic scope (intracountry). (12,361 rows). Fee rules table. NULL in any dimension = wildcard (matches all). ALL matching rules are summed — no ''most specific wins'' logic.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fees.ID IS '[identifier] Primary key for fee records. (BIGINT, 1,232 distinct, range: 1..1000)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fees.card_scheme IS '[categorical] Payment network brand associated with the transaction fee. (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, range: GlobalCard..TransactPlus, avg 10 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fees.capture_delay IS '[categorical] Categorical time range or trigger for payment capture. Values: manual, immediate, or day-based buckets (<3, 3-5, >5). High nullity (52%). (VARCHAR, 5 distinct, 52% null, range: 3-5..manual, avg 5 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fees.monthly_fraud_level IS '[categorical] Binned percentage ranges representing monthly fraud risk tiers. High nullity (90.2%). Values: <7.2%, 7.2%-7.7%, 7.7%-8.3%, >8.3%. (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, 90% null, range: 7.2%-7.7%..>8.3%, avg 7 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fees.monthly_volume IS '[categorical] Binned categorical ranges representing transaction volume tiers. High nullity (79.4%). Values: <100k, 100k-1m, 1m-5m, >5m. (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, 79% null, range: 100k-1m..>5m, avg 5 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fees.is_credit IS '[flag] Indicates if fee is a credit (True) or a debit (False). (BOOLEAN, 2 distinct, 9% null, range: false..true)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fees.fixed_amount IS '[measure] Static monetary surcharge applied to fee calculations. (DOUBLE, 13 distinct, range: 0.0..0.14)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fees.rate IS '[measure] Numerical fee percentage or basis points; range 10-99. (BIGINT, 82 distinct, range: 10..99). Basis points. rate=75 means 0.75% of transaction value.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fees.intracountry IS '[flag] Binary indicator for domestic vs. international fee application; 1.0 for internal, 0.0 for cross-border. (DOUBLE, 2 distinct, 55% null, range: 0.0..1.0). 1.0=domestic, 0.0=international, NULL=both.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fees.account_type IS '[categorical] Single-character fee classification code; 62% null rate; values: S, F, R, H. (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, 62% null, range: D..S, avg 1 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fees.aci IS '[categorical] Single-character fee category or adjustment code. (VARCHAR, 6 distinct, 7% null, range: A..F, avg 1 chars). Values A-G possible. fee_rules_expanded only covers A-F.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fees.merchant_category_code IS '[categorical] ISO 18245 standard four-digit code classifying merchant business type. Values 3000-9399. (BIGINT, 57 distinct, 2% null, range: 3000..9399)';

-- View: fraud_aci_costs
COMMENT ON VIEW main.fraud_aci_costs IS 'Monthly fraud processing costs and transaction volumes by merchant. Tracks `derived_total_fee` and `derived_fraud_txn_count` against `derived_target_aci` benchmarks. Primary keys: `payments_merchant`, `payments_year`, `derived_month`. Use for merchant-level fraud overhead analysis and ACI performance tracking. (360 rows). Pre-computed ACI steering for fraud: total fee if all fraudulent transactions were redirected to each candidate ACI (A-F). card_scheme joined with exact match (no NULL wildcard). Target ACIs A-F only, G excluded.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fraud_aci_costs.payments_merchant IS '[categorical] Merchant trade name associated with ACI fraud processing costs. (VARCHAR, 5 distinct, range: Belles_cookbook_store..Rafa_AI, avg 17 chars). Merchant name. Filter for merchant-specific fraud ACI analysis.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fraud_aci_costs.payments_year IS '[date] Calendar year of payment processing. (BIGINT, 1 distinct, range: 2023..2023). Transaction year.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fraud_aci_costs.derived_month IS '[categorical] Calendar month integer extracted from transaction timestamp. (BIGINT, 13 distinct, range: 1..12). Calendar month (1-12). Aggregate across months for yearly questions.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fraud_aci_costs.derived_target_aci IS '[categorical] Single-character fraud target classification code derived from ACI cost metrics. (VARCHAR, 6 distinct, range: A..F, avg 1 chars). Candidate ACI (A-F) that fraud transactions would be redirected to.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fraud_aci_costs.derived_total_fee IS '[measure] Calculated aggregate fee amount associated with fraud analysis costs. (DOUBLE, 347 distinct, range: 2.9128339999999997..637.3176559999997). Total fee in EUR if all fraud transactions for this merchant/month used this ACI.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.fraud_aci_costs.derived_fraud_txn_count IS '[measure] Aggregated count of fraudulent transactions derived from ACI cost data. (BIGINT, 160 distinct, range: 7..396). Number of fraudulent transactions for this merchant/month.';

-- Table: merchant_category_codes
COMMENT ON TABLE main.merchant_category_codes IS 'Standard ISO 18245 Merchant Category Codes (MCC) mapping four-digit classification codes to business category descriptions. Primary reference for transaction categorization and merchant industry identification. (769 rows)';

COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_category_codes.row_index IS '[identifier] Zero-based sequential record index. (BIGINT, 969 distinct, range: 0..768)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_category_codes.mcc IS '[categorical] Four-digit ISO 18245 merchant category code identifying business type. (VARCHAR, 777 distinct, range: 0742..9950, avg 4 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_category_codes.description IS '[categorical] Official industry name or service classification associated with a Merchant Category Code (MCC). (VARCHAR, 876 distinct, range: A-1 RENT-A-CAR..ZAMBIA AIRWAYS, avg 24 chars)';

-- View: merchant_transaction_fees
COMMENT ON VIEW main.merchant_transaction_fees IS 'Granular merchant transaction ledger mapping payments to fee structures. Links `payments_merchant` to `merchants_account_type` and `merchants_mcc`. Contains transaction metadata (card scheme, ACI, credit status, cross-border geography), fraud indicators, and calculated fee components (`fees_fixed_amount`, `fees_rate`, `derived_fee_amount`). Aggregated metrics include `derived_monthly_volume` and `derived_monthly_fraud_pct`. Primary use: fee reconciliation, fraud impact analysis, and volume-based pricing segmentation via `derived_volume_range` and `derived_fraud_level_range`. (137,433 rows). Each row = one payment matched to one fee rule. Rows duplicated per matching fee. SUM derived_fee_amount for total fees. Do NOT SUM payments_eur_amount or COUNT payments — use payments table for those.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.payments_merchant IS '[categorical] Merchant business name associated with transaction fees. (VARCHAR, 5 distinct, range: Belles_cookbook_store..Rafa_AI, avg 17 chars). Filter on this for merchant-specific fee queries.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.payments_year IS '[date] Calendar year of fee assessment. (BIGINT, 1 distinct, range: 2023..2023). Transaction year. Combine with derived_month for time filtering.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.payments_day_of_year IS '[date] Ordinal day of the year for fee processing, ranging 1 to 365. (BIGINT, 383 distinct, range: 1..365). 1-365. Use derived_month for monthly aggregations.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.payments_eur_amount IS '[measure] Transaction fee amount in Euros. (DOUBLE, 18,368 distinct, range: 0.88..3888.59). WARNING: duplicated per fee rule — do NOT SUM. Use payments table for transaction volume.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.payments_card_scheme IS '[categorical] Card network or payment processor brand name. (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, range: GlobalCard..TransactPlus, avg 11 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.payments_aci IS '[categorical] Single-character ACI (Authorization Characteristics Indicator) code for payment processing classification. (VARCHAR, 7 distinct, range: A..G, avg 1 chars). ACI of original transaction. GROUP BY for ''most expensive ACI'' questions.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.payments_is_credit IS '[flag] Indicates if the transaction fee applies to a credit card payment versus a debit or alternative method. (BOOLEAN, 2 distinct, range: false..true)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.payments_issuing_country IS '[categorical] ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 code for the payment instrument''s country of origin. (VARCHAR, 9 distinct, range: BE..SE, avg 2 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.payments_acquirer_country IS '[categorical] ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 code of the payment acquirer''s jurisdiction. (VARCHAR, 5 distinct, range: FR..US, avg 2 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.payments_has_fraudulent_dispute IS '[flag] Indicates if the transaction fee is associated with a payment marked by a fraudulent dispute. (BOOLEAN, 2 distinct, range: false..true). Do NOT COUNT for fraud rate — rows duplicated. Use payments table.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.derived_intracountry IS '[flag] Boolean indicator for domestic transactions within the same country. 1.0 for intracountry, 0.0 for cross-border. (DECIMAL(2,1), 2 distinct, range: 0.0..1.0). 1.0=domestic, 0.0=international. Derived from issuing_country = acquirer_country.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.derived_month IS '[categorical] Calendar month integer extracted from transaction date. (BIGINT, 13 distinct, range: 1..12). Calendar month (1-12) derived from day_of_year.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.derived_fee_amount IS '[measure] Calculated monetary fee applied to merchant transactions. (DOUBLE, 117,435 distinct, range: 0.0041800000000000006..32.295297000000005). Pre-computed: fees_fixed_amount + (fees_rate / 10000.0) * payments_eur_amount. SUM this for total fees.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.fees_id IS '[identifier] Primary key for merchant transaction fee records. (BIGINT, 115 distinct, range: 12..996). Fee rule ID. A transaction may match multiple fee rules (multiple fees_id values).';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.fees_fixed_amount IS '[measure] Flat-rate monetary surcharge per transaction in merchant currency. (DOUBLE, 13 distinct, range: 0.0..0.14)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.fees_rate IS '[measure] Merchant transaction fee percentage represented in basis points. (BIGINT, 58 distinct, range: 10..99). Basis points. Fee = fees_fixed_amount + (fees_rate / 10000.0) * payments_eur_amount.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.merchants_account_type IS '[categorical] Merchant account classification code; values: R, F, D, H. (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, range: D..R, avg 1 chars). From merchants dimension. One of: R, D, H, F, S, O.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.merchants_mcc IS '[categorical] ISO 18245 Merchant Category Code (MCC) identifying business type. (BIGINT, 5 distinct, range: 5812..7997). Merchant category code (BIGINT). From merchants dimension.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.derived_capture_delay_range IS '[categorical] Categorical delay between transaction authorization and capture. Values: ''immediate'', ''manual'', or numeric day ranges (''<3'', ''>5''). (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, range: <3..manual, avg 5 chars). Bucketed from merchant capture_delay: <3, 3-5, >5, immediate, manual.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.derived_monthly_volume IS '[measure] Calculated aggregate monthly transaction value per merchant. (DOUBLE, 66 distinct, range: 91877.05000000006..438023.58999999997). Monthly aggregate for fee rule matching only. Do NOT use for per-transaction fees.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.derived_monthly_fraud_pct IS '[measure] Calculated monthly fraud rate percentage per merchant. (DOUBLE, 64 distinct, range: 6.096798094222417..11.615551224247673). Monthly fraud percentage (0-100 scale). Fee matching uses derived_fraud_level_range.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.derived_volume_range IS '[categorical] Binned merchant transaction volume bracket for fee tiering. (VARCHAR, 2 distinct, range: 100k-1m..<100k, avg 7 chars). Monthly volume bucket: <100k, 100k-1m, 1m-5m, >5m.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchant_transaction_fees.derived_fraud_level_range IS '[categorical] Binned merchant fraud rate intervals used for fee calculation. (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, range: 7.2%-7.7%..>8.3%, avg 6 chars). Monthly fraud bucket: <7.2%, 7.2%-7.7%, 7.7%-8.3%, >8.3%.';

-- Table: merchants
COMMENT ON TABLE main.merchants IS 'Merchant configuration mapping for transaction processing. Links `merchant` identifiers to `acquirer` routing, `merchant_category_code` (MCC), and `account_type`. Defines `capture_delay` intervals for settlement timing. 30 rows. (30 rows). Dimension table (~30 rows). Only 5 merchants appear in payments. Properties: account_type, MCC, capture_delay.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchants.merchant IS '[categorical] Unique merchant name; 35 distinct values ranging from AI_Pro_Labs to Yoga_Masters. (VARCHAR, 35 distinct, range: AI_Pro_Labs..Yoga_Masters, avg 13 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchants.capture_delay IS '[categorical] Payment capture timing policy: ''immediate'', ''manual'', or integer string representing delay in days. (VARCHAR, 5 distinct, range: 1..manual, avg 4 chars). VARCHAR. Numeric values bucketed for fee matching via TRY_CAST.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchants.acquirer IS '[categorical] Array of financial institutions processing merchant transactions. (VARCHAR[], 18 distinct, range: [bank_of_springfield]..[the_savings_and_loan_bank, da, avg 28 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchants.merchant_category_code IS '[categorical] ISO 18245 standard four-digit code classifying merchant business type. (BIGINT, 7 distinct, range: 5812..8299). BIGINT. Used for fee rule matching.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.merchants.account_type IS '[categorical] Merchant account classification code; single-character internal category (F, S, H, R). (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, range: D..S, avg 1 chars)';

-- Table: payments
COMMENT ON TABLE main.payments IS 'Transaction-level payment data for fraud analysis and authorization monitoring. Contains PSP references, merchant IDs, card metadata (scheme, BIN, credit/debit), and temporal features (year, day, hour, minute). Includes risk indicators (`has_fraudulent_dispute`, `is_refused_by_adyen`), transaction amounts in EUR, and PII for identity linking (`ip_address`, `email_address`, `card_number`). Supports analysis of approval rates, geographic risk (IP vs. issuing country), and device-based fraud patterns. (138,236 rows). Core transaction table. One row per payment. Use this for transaction counts, volumes, and fraud rates — NOT the fee views which duplicate rows.';

COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.psp_reference IS '[identifier] Unique external payment service provider transaction reference number. (BIGINT, 143,246 distinct, range: 10000636248..89998294921)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.merchant IS '[categorical] Merchant name associated with the payment; low-cardinality categorical string. (VARCHAR, 5 distinct, range: Belles_cookbook_store..Rafa_AI, avg 15 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.card_scheme IS '[categorical] Payment network brand name. Categorical value with 4 distinct alpha-only entries. (VARCHAR, 4 distinct, range: GlobalCard..TransactPlus, avg 9 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.year IS '[date] Calendar year of payment transaction. (BIGINT, 1 distinct, range: 2023..2023)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.hour_of_day IS '[categorical] Hour of transaction in 24-hour format. (BIGINT, 24 distinct, range: 0..23)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.minute_of_hour IS '[measure] Minute component of payment timestamp; integer range 0-59. (BIGINT, 54 distinct, range: 0..59)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.day_of_year IS '[date] Ordinal day of the calendar year for payment occurrence. (BIGINT, 383 distinct, range: 1..365). 1-365. Convert to date: MAKE_DATE(year, 1, 1) + INTERVAL (day_of_year - 1) DAY.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.is_credit IS '[flag] Boolean indicator distinguishing credit transactions from other payment types. (BOOLEAN, 2 distinct, range: false..true)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.eur_amount IS '[measure] Transaction value in Euros. Range 0.50 to 4811.76; mean 91.85. (DOUBLE, 25,311 distinct, range: 0.5..4811.76)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.ip_country IS '[categorical] ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code derived from payment IP address. (VARCHAR, 9 distinct, range: BE..SE, avg 2 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.issuing_country IS '[categorical] ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 code of the payment card issuer. (VARCHAR, 9 distinct, range: BE..SE, avg 2 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.device_type IS '[categorical] Operating system or hardware platform used for transaction. Categorical values: Android, Other, iOS, MacOS, Linux. (VARCHAR, 6 distinct, range: Android..iOS, avg 5 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.ip_address IS '[identifier] Anonymized or hashed IPv4/IPv6 address associated with payment origin. 20% null rate. High-cardinality alphanumeric strings. (VARCHAR, 58,995 distinct, 20% null, range: --2MGnvvdwjX1O5uXHk4Mg..zzlHcw3JCpVdYURGKfEvRA, avg 22 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.email_address IS '[text] Customer email contact for payment notifications; 10% null rate; contains alphanumeric strings with standard delimiters. (VARCHAR, 38,097 distinct, 10% null, range: --1ybOIvbbdtxkAx3pFRgQ..zzlacMoh8cvOKMdegSuHiA, avg 22 chars). Customer identifier. ''Customer'' = email_address, NOT card_number.';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.card_number IS '[identifier] Encrypted or masked credit card identifier; alphanumeric string with special characters. (VARCHAR, 52,597 distinct, range: --Eieag66O2wS9sh3aKGrw..zzzp-SYj0U6e5r2ioWVniQ, avg 22 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.shopper_interaction IS '[categorical] Payment channel classification; restricted to ''POS'' or ''Ecommerce''. (VARCHAR, 2 distinct, range: Ecommerce..POS, avg 8 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.card_bin IS '[categorical] First four to six digits of the credit card number identifying the issuing institution. (BIGINT, 13 distinct, range: 4017..4920)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.has_fraudulent_dispute IS '[flag] Indicates if a payment was contested as unauthorized or fraudulent. (BOOLEAN, 2 distinct, range: false..true). Boolean. Fraud rate = SUM(CASE WHEN true THEN eur_amount) / SUM(eur_amount).';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.is_refused_by_adyen IS '[flag] Indicates if the Adyen payment gateway rejected the transaction attempt. (BOOLEAN, 2 distinct, range: false..true)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.aci IS '[categorical] Single-character payment status or authorization code. (VARCHAR, 7 distinct, range: A..G, avg 1 chars)';
COMMENT ON COLUMN main.payments.acquirer_country IS '[categorical] ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 code of the payment processor''s country. (VARCHAR, 5 distinct, range: FR..US, avg 2 chars)';
